{"id": "duc04-testb-6:3#10", "contents": "The water supply in North Korea is also a major concern. Red Cross representatives tested the water supply at 840 hospitals and clinics and found that not one had water suitable for human consumption. Sten Swedlund, head of the Red Cross delegation in North Korea, said that people have no choice but to drink the water, which is closely linked to the problems caused by the lack of food and a health sector in very bad shape. Virtually all children under 7 who are malnourished also have diarrhea, highlighting the close relationship between hunger and poor health."}
